  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Central)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Proficient in interpreting technical drawings and performing accurate measurements.</li>\n  <li>Skilled in preparing comprehensive Bills of Quantities (BQ).</li>\n  <li>Well-versed in reviewing and understanding tenders, contracts, specifications, and contractual terms.</li>\n  <li>Capable of analyzing quotations, pricing structures, and rate build-ups for accurate cost estimation.</li>\n  <li>Experienced in contract administration, including valuation of progress payments and variation claims in compliance with contract terms.</li>\n  <li>Adept at managing tender processes and procurement activities for new projects.</li>\n  <li>Able to support other business functions and activities of the holding company as required.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrates strong ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team.</li>\n  <li>Willing to participate in company-related initiatives such as CSR or charity events.</li>\n  <li>Committed to delivering assigned responsibilities within deadlines and operational constraints.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
